<AbstractNarration>The Department of Statistics at North Carolina State University will&lt;br/&gt;purchase a high-performance clustered computing facility which will be&lt;br/&gt;dedicated to the support of research in the mathematical sciences. The&lt;br/&gt;equipment will be used for several research projects, including in&lt;br/&gt;particular:   &lt;br/&gt; - Simulation Methods for Data Measured With Error   &lt;br/&gt; - Stochastic Models of Gene Regulation   &lt;br/&gt; - Spatial Modeling, Visualization and Inference   &lt;br/&gt; - Statistical Analysis of Large Data Sets   &lt;br/&gt; - Models of Biological Pattern Formation&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
